kind of crazy.

72
00:05:55,270 --> 00:05:57,005
Psychopaths are not crazy.

73
00:05:57,072 --> 00:05:59,373
They're fully aware
of what they do

74
00:05:59,441 --> 00:06:01,744
and the consequences
of those actions.

75
00:06:01,811 --> 00:06:06,015
Would you diagnose someone
like Tobias as a psychopath?

76
00:06:06,082 --> 00:06:09,318
Or, uh, are you supposed
to diagnose other people

77
00:06:09,386 --> 00:06:12,923
in front of me? Do you... would
you rather just talk about me?

78
00:06:12,990 --> 00:06:14,926
Not at all.

79
00:06:14,993 --> 00:06:17,695
Are you bored with me?

80
00:06:17,763 --> 00:06:19,459
No.

81
00:06:19,579 --> 00:06:20,847
This is your hour,
Franklyn.

82
00:06:20,967 --> 00:06:23,831
We will talk about whatever
you would like to talk about.

83
00:06:24,136 --> 00:06:26,772
I'd like to talk about Tobias.
Perhaps you can

84
00:06:26,839 --> 00:06:29,175
- help me analyze him.
- I'm not analyzing

85
00:06:29,242 --> 00:06:31,578
your friend; I'm analyzing
your perception of him.

86
00:06:31,645 --> 00:06:35,115
It may help you know yourself
better. You could be

87
00:06:35,183 --> 00:06:38,052
