whose throat was cut

193
00:14:50,560 --> 00:14:52,628
and played like a violin.

194
00:14:54,352 --> 00:14:57,071
So you think Tobias killed
that man at the symphony?

195
00:14:57,191 --> 00:14:58,617
I don't know.

196
00:14:58,737 --> 00:15:00,839
I-I...

197
00:15:03,142 --> 00:15:05,643
If I do, do I have
to report it?

198
00:15:05,711 --> 00:15:07,579
Do you have a reason not to?

199
00:15:07,646 --> 00:15:09,214
What if I'm wrong?

200
00:15:09,282 --> 00:15:11,251
What if you're right?

201
00:15:11,318 --> 00:15:13,052
I'm always wrong.

202
00:15:13,120 --> 00:15:17,624
I don't know. Why would he say
something like that to me?

203
00:15:17,692 --> 00:15:20,461
Why do you think?

204
00:15:23,298 --> 00:15:25,767
'Cause he knows I'd tell you.

205
00:16:00,874 --> 00:16:03,277
You're Franklyn's therapist,
Dr. Lecter.

206
00:16:03,345 --> 00:16:05,246
- Nice to see you again.
- Is it Tobias?

207
00:16:05,314 --> 00:16:06,748
Yes.

208
00:16:06,816 --> 00:16:08,750
Your strings are all gut.

209
00:16:08,818 --> 00:16:11,753
I also carry steel and polymer
strings, if you prefer.

210
00:16:11,821 --> 00:16:13,355
