00:19:49,845 --> 00:19:53,182
I can stop the thinking
if we're not...

257
00:19:53,249 --> 00:19:56,885
- But if we're...
- Intimate.

258
00:19:59,490 --> 00:20:02,626
The way that I am
in relationships...

259
00:20:02,694 --> 00:20:05,396
Not that this is a relationship;
it's just a kiss.

260
00:20:07,865 --> 00:20:09,466
A great kiss.

261
00:20:09,534 --> 00:20:11,969
But I...

262
00:20:12,037 --> 00:20:14,206
the way that I am isn't

263
00:20:14,273 --> 00:20:17,577
- compatible with the way that...
- The way I am.

264
00:20:23,117 --> 00:20:24,983
I wouldn't be good for you.

265
00:20:25,051 --> 00:20:28,088
You wouldn't be good for me,
and I wouldn't be able

266
00:20:28,155 --> 00:20:30,758
to stop analyzing,
because I have this

267
00:20:30,826 --> 00:20:33,894
professional curiosity
about you and...

268
00:20:41,170 --> 00:20:43,973
I am not your patient.

269
00:20:46,677 --> 00:20:48,211
If I were

270
00:20:48,279 --> 00:20:51,582
my patient, my advice to me...

271
00:20:51,650 --> 00:20:53,985
don't do this.

272
00:20:54,053 --> 00:20:58,223
I have to follow my own advice.

273
00:21:06,900 --> 00:21:09,936
I'm gonna go ahead
and go now.

274
00:21:10,004 --> 00:21:12,037
Goodnight, Will.

275
00:21:25,689 --> 00:21:28,724
More wine?

276
00:21:31,095 --> 00:21:34,531
A late harvest Vidal
from Linden.

277
00:21:34,599 --> 00:21:37,568
Oh, Virginia.
I thought it was French.

278
00:21:37,636 --> 00:21:40,070
The Virginia wine revolution
is upon us.

279
00:21:42,041 --> 00:21:44,275
I apologize for being
so blunt, Tobias,

280
00:21:44,343 --> 00:21:46,345
but I have to ask.

281
00:21:46,413 --> 00:21:50,149
Did you kill that trombonist?

282
00:21:50,217 --> 00:21:52,585
Do you really have to ask?

283
00:21:52,653 --> 00:21:55,956
No. Just changing the subject.

284
00:21:56,024 --> 00:21:58,959
Franklyn gave you my message.

285
00:21:59,027 --> 00:22:02,596
The murder is being
investigated by the FBI.

286
00:22:02,664 --> 00:22:04,633
They're going to find you.

287
00:22:04,701 --> 00:22:06,968
Let them.

288
00:22:07,036 --> 00:22:08,971
You want to get caught?

289
00:22:09,039 --> 00:22:11,140
I want them to try.

290
00:22:11,208 --> 00:22:13,142
They may investigate me

291
00:22:13,210 --> 00:22:15,812
because I own a string shop.

292
00:22:15,879 --> 00:22:18,148
They'll send men
to investigate,

293
00:22:18,216 --> 00:22:20,150
and I'll kill them.

294
00:22:20,218 --> 00:22:22,519
Then I'll find Franklyn
and kill him.

295
00:22:22,587 --> 00:22:25,022
Then I would disappear.

296
00:22:27,125 --> 00:22:30,028
- Don't kill Franklyn.
- I've been looking forward to it.

297
00:22:30,096 --> 00:22:31,863
Actually...

298
00:22:34,735 --> 00:22:37,704
- I was going to kill you.
- Of course you were.

299
00:22:37,772 --> 00:22:39,339
I'm lean.

300
00:22:39,407 --> 00:22:41,508
Lean animals yield
the toughest gut.

301
00:22:41,577 --> 00:22:44,645
What stopped you
from wanting to kill me?

302
00:22:44,713 --> 00:22:47,515
Or have you stopped?

303
00:22:47,583 --> 00:22:51,854
I stopped after I followed you
one night. Out of town.

304
00:22:51,921 --> 00:22:53,856
To a lonely road.

305
00:22:53,923 --> 00:22:55,958
To a bus yard.

306
00:23:03,868 --> 00:23:05,936
You're reckless, Tobias.

307
00:23:06,004 --> 00:23:10,975
I'm not going to tell anyone
what I saw you do and do well.

308
00:23:11,043 --> 00:23:14,881
So my recklessness doesn't
concern you.

309
00:23:14,948 --> 00:23:16,949
It concerns me

310
00:23:17,017 --> 00:23:20,185
because you won't be drawing
attention just to yourself.

311
00:23:30,165 --> 00:23:32,333
I could use a friend.

312
00:23:32,401 --> 00:23:34,737
Someone who can
understand me.

313
00:23:34,805 --> 00:23:38,340
Who thinks like I do and can see
the world and the people in it

314
00:23:38,408 --> 00:23:40,342
the way I do.

315
00:23:40,410 --> 00:23:42,578
I know exactly how you feel.

316
00:23:42,646 --> 00:23:45,582
But I don't want
to be your friend.

317
00:23:45,650 --> 00:23:49,053
Then why did you invite me
here for dinner?

318
00:23:49,120 --> 00:23:52,356
Wasn't just to restring
your harpsichord.

319
00:23:52,424 --> 00:23:54,692
I was going to kill you.

320
00:23:54,760 --> 00:23:57,596
I didn't poison you, Tobias.

321
00:23:57,664 --> 00:24:00,065
I wouldn't do that to the food.

322
00:24:06,675 --> 00:24:08,808
Expecting someone?

323
00:24:08,876 --> 00:24:11,078
No.

324
00:24:21,992 --> 00:24:24,926
Well, I kissed Alana Bloom.

325
00:24:27,297 --> 00:24:30,000
Well, come in.

326
00:24:30,067 --> 00:24:32,135
You have a guest?

327
00:24:32,203 --> 00:24:35,373
A colleague.
You just missed him.

328
00:24:35,440 --> 00:24:37,074
Didn't finish his dinner.

329
00:24:37,142 --> 00:24:40,244
An urgent call of some sort.
He had to leave suddenly.

330
00:24:40,312 --> 00:24:41,846
This benefits you,

331
00:24:41,914 --> 00:24:44,249
because I have dessert for two.

332
00:24:47,721 --> 00:24:49,222
Tell me,

333
00:24:49,289 --> 00:24:51,457
what was Alana's reaction?

334
00:24:51,526 --> 00:24:54,595
She said she wouldn't be good
for me,

335
00:24:54,663 --> 00:24:57,764
and I wouldn't be good for her.

336
00:24:57,832 --> 00:25:00,068
I don't disagree.

337
00:25:00,136 --> 00:25:03,339
She would feel an obligation to her
field of study to observe you,

338
00:25:03,407 --> 00:25:05,508
and you would resent her for it.

339
00:25:05,575 --> 00:25:07,577
- I know.
- Wondering then

340
00:25:07,645 --> 00:25:10,313
why you kissed her,
and felt compelled

341
00:25:10,381 --> 00:25:12,882
to drive an hour in the snow
to tell me about it.

342
00:25:12,950 --> 00:25:16,653
Well, I wanted to kiss her
since I met her. She's very kissable.

343
00:25:16,721 --> 00:25:19,657
You waited a long time,

344
00:25:19,724 --> 00:25:22,294
which suggests you were
kissing her for a reason,

345
00:25:22,362 --> 00:25:24,296
in addition to wanting to.

346
00:25:24,364 --> 00:25:27,867
I heard an animal
trapped in my chimney.

347
00:25:27,935 --> 00:25:29,568
Um...

348
00:25:29,635 --> 00:25:33,373
Broke through the wall
to get it out.

349
00:25:33,441 --> 00:25:35,809
Didn't find anything inside.

350
00:25:37,045 --> 00:25:40,348
Alana showed up,
she looked at me...

351
00:25:40,416 --> 00:25:43,952
I... maybe her face changed.

352
00:25:44,019 --> 00:25:46,121
I don't know.

353
00:25:46,189 --> 00:25:48,390
But, um, she knew.

354
00:25:52,028 --> 00:25:54,230
What did she know, Will?

355
00:25:54,298 --> 00:25:57,468
There was no animal
in the chimney.

356
00:25:57,535 --> 00:25:59,604
It was only in my head.

357
00:25:59,671 --> 00:26:02,839
I sleepwalk.

358
00:26:02,907 --> 00:26:05,543
I get headaches.

359
00:26:05,611 --> 00:26:07,645
I am hearing things.

360
00:26:10,450 --> 00:26:13,051
I feel unstable.

361
00:26:13,120 --> 00:26:15,188
That's why you kissed her.

362
00:26:15,256 --> 00:26:17,189
A clutch for balance.

363
00:26:19,927 --> 00:26:23,264
You said yourself
what you do is not good for you.

364
00:26:23,332 --> 00:26:25,833
Well, unfortunately,
I am good for it.

365
00:26:25,900 --> 00:26:29,438
Are you still hearing
this killer's serenade

366
00:26:29,506 --> 00:26:31,273
behind your eyes?

367
00:26:31,341 --> 00:26:33,475
Well, it's our song.

368
00:26:50,128 --> 00:26:53,898
I hesitate telling you this, as it
borders on a violation of doctor-patient

369
00:26:53,966 --> 00:26:56,001
confidentiality.

370
00:26:59,606 --> 00:27:02,176
A patient told me today
he suspects a friend of his may

371
00:27:02,243 --> 00:27:04,610
be involved with the murder
at the symphony.

372
00:27:07,114 --> 00:27:08,915
Right, um...

373
00:27:11,787 --> 00:27:14,690
Um... what did he say
about his friend?

374
00:27:14,757 --> 00:27:17,077
He owns a music store
in Baltimore,

375
00:27:17,197 --> 00:27:20,329
specializing
in string instruments.

376
00:27:20,397 --> 00:27:22,864
Perhaps
you should interview him.

377
00:27:24,835 --> 00:27:26,436
Yeah.

378
00:27:30,455 --> 00:27:34,359
For the first time in a long while,
I see a possibility of friendship.

379
00:27:35,876 --> 00:27:37,494
Is there someone new
in your life?

380
00:27:37,614 --> 00:27:39,895
I met a man much like myself.

381
00:27:40,015 --> 00:27:42,435
Same hobbies, same worldviews,

382
00:27:42,504 --> 00:27:45,805
but I'm not interested in being his friend.
I'm curious about him,

383
00:27:45,873 --> 00:27:48,308
and that got me curious
about friendship.

384
00:27:48,376 --> 00:27:51,645
Whose friendship
are you considering?

385
00:27:51,713 --> 00:27:54,549
Oddly enough, a colleague
and a patient,

386
00:27:54,617 --> 00:27:57,386
not unlike how I'm a colleague
and a patient of yours.

387
00:27:57,454 --> 00:27:59,321
We've discussed him before.

388
00:27:59,389 --> 00:28:01,356
- Will Graham.
- He's nothing like me.

389
00:28:01,425 --> 00:28:04,960
We see the world
in different ways,

390
00:28:05,028 --> 00:28:07,964
yet he can
assume my point of view.

391
00:28:08,032 --> 00:28:11,803
By profiling
the criminally insane.

392
00:28:11,870 --> 00:28:14,739
As good a demonstration as any.

393
00:28:14,807 --> 00:28:17,542
I find it reassuring.

394
00:28:17,609 --> 00:28:20,612
It's nice
when someone sees us, Hannibal.

395
00:28:20,680 --> 00:28:24,683
Or has the ability to see us.

396
00:28:25,152 --> 00:28:27,253
It requires trust.

397
00:28:27,321 --> 00:28:31,091
Trust is difficult for you.

398
00:28:31,159 --> 00:28:33,559
You've helped me
to better understand what I want

399
00:28:33,626 --> 00:28:36,429
in a friendship,
and what I don't.

400
00:28:36,497 --> 00:28:39,267
Someone worthy
of your friendship.

401
00:28:39,335 --> 00:28:41,702
- Yes.
- You spend

402
00:28:41,770 --> 00:28:44,606
a lot of time
building walls, Hannibal.

403
00:28:44,674 --> 00:28:46,775
It's natural to want to see

404
00:28:46,843 --> 00:28:50,753
if someone is clever enough
to climb over them.

405
00:28:54,718 --> 00:28:56,652
<i>JSB's Suite No.1.</i>

406
00:28:56,720 --> 00:28:58,689
Okay.

407
00:28:58,757 --> 00:29:01,926
Special agent Will Graham
with the FBI.

408
00:29:01,994 --> 00:29:05,010
- Are you the owner?
- Yes. Tobias Budge.

409
00:29:05,130 --> 00:29:08,299
I'm just showing one of my students out.
Can I have a moment?

410
00:29:08,367 --> 00:29:10,535
Adagio.

411
00:29:10,603 --> 00:29:12,705
For Saturday.

412
00:29:15,842 --> 00:29:18,177
What can I help you with?

413
00:29:18,245 --> 00:29:21,415
We're investigating the death
of Douglas Wilson. He was...

414
00:29:21,482 --> 00:29:22,916
The trombonist.

415
00:29:22,983 --> 00:29:24,918
That's right.
Did you know him?

416
00:29:24,985 --> 00:29:26,220
I was aware of him.

417
00:29:26,288 --> 00:29:28,823
Baltimore is a small town,

418
00:29:28,891 --> 00:29:32,928
and the cultural arts community
is an even smaller one.

419
00:29:32,995 --> 00:29:35,297
Well, that's why
we're here, Mr. Budge.

420
00:29:35,365 --> 00:29:37,767
I hear someone cut his throat
and tried to play it with a bow.

421
00:29:39,736 --> 00:29:41,604
Why do you say "try"?

422
00:29:41,672 --> 00:29:44,374
The strings have to be treated.

423
00:29:44,442 --> 00:29:47,011
You can't just
open somebody up and draw a bow

424
00:29:47,079 --> 00:29:49,447
across their innards
and expect to produce a sound.

425
00:29:51,584 --> 00:29:56,388
The vocal chords were chemically treated, uh,
similar to how catgut string is treated.

426
00:29:56,456 --> 00:29:59,859
We kept those details
out of the press.

427
00:29:59,927 --> 00:30:02,996
Looking for someone who knows
how to manufacture gut strings?

428
00:30:03,064 --> 00:30:04,999
Anybody leap to mind?

429
00:30:05,067 --> 00:30:07,034
Mine are imported from Italy.

430
00:30:07,102 --> 00:30:09,037
Best catgut is.

431
00:30:09,105 --> 00:30:11,038
The string section
of the Baltimore Metropolitan

432
00:30:11,106 --> 00:30:13,275
Orchestra refuses
to play anything else.

433
00:30:13,343 --> 00:30:14,776
More authentic.

434
00:30:14,844 --> 00:30:17,612
A richer, darker sound.

435
00:30:17,681 --> 00:30:21,017
Allows music
to say what words can't.

436
00:30:26,556 --> 00:30:29,793
Something wrong?

437
00:30:29,861 --> 00:30:33,131
Didn't you hear that?

438
00:30:33,199 --> 00:30:37,003
I didn't hear anything.

439
00:30:37,070 --> 00:30:39,205
Excuse me a minute.

440
00:31:09,441 --> 00:31:11,608
Sorry about that.

441
00:31:18,550 --> 00:31:20,152
Officers?

442
00:31:22,121 --> 00:31:23,656
Officers?

443
00:31:47,005 --> 00:31:49,710
I need ERT at Chordophone
Strings, downtown Baltimore.

444
00:31:49,830 --> 00:31:51,092
Officer down.

445
00:34:06,777 --> 00:34:09,012
Nine.

446
00:34:09,080 --> 00:34:11,080
Nine times.

447
00:34:11,148 --> 00:34:14,151
I can count on two hands
the number of times I've been

448
00:34:14,219 --> 00:34:16,787
dumped by a psychiatrist.
I'm sorry, Franklyn,

449
00:34:16,855 --> 00:34:19,458
but I think you should
see another doctor.

450
00:34:19,525 --> 00:34:21,593
- You're giving me a referral?
- Yes, I am.

451
00:34:21,661 --> 00:34:24,397
- You were a referral!
- I am also a part of the problem.

452
00:34:24,465 --> 00:34:26,831
You focus too much

453
00:34:26,899 --> 00:34:30,236
on your therapist,
and not enough on your therapy.

454
00:34:30,304 --> 00:34:34,007
You lost respect for me
because I wouldn't

455
00:34:34,075 --> 00:34:37,779
- report Tobias, didn't you?
- Report Tobias for what?

456
00:34:40,983 --> 00:34:42,417
Tobias.

457
00:34:42,485 --> 00:34:44,686
I came to say goodbye,
Franklyn.

458
00:34:44,754 --> 00:34:47,089
What do you mean, goodbye?

459
00:34:47,157 --> 00:34:49,091
Oh, my God.

460
00:34:49,159 --> 00:34:52,429
Oh, my God, is that your blood?
I just killed two men.

461
00:34:52,497 --> 00:34:55,966
The police came to question me
about the murder.

462
00:34:59,938 --> 00:35:02,873
Ok... you have

463
00:35:02,941 --> 00:35:04,976
to give yourself up right now.

464
00:35:05,044 --> 00:35:08,347
This plane is going down.

465
00:35:08,415 --> 00:35:10,883
Let it have
a controlled descent.

466
00:35:10,951 --> 00:35:13,052
We can get you back up
in the air again.

467
00:35:13,120 --> 00:35:15,322
There's rehabilitation
for everyone.

468
00:35:15,389 --> 00:35:17,791
Franklyn, I want you
to leave now.

469
00:35:17,858 --> 00:35:20,795
Stay right where you are,
Franklyn.

470
00:35:22,764 --> 00:35:25,066
You've done

471
00:35:25,134 --> 00:35:27,336
a horrible thing,

472
00:35:27,403 --> 00:35:30,872
and... I know...

473
00:35:30,940 --> 00:35:33,409
that you wish to God
that you didn't.

474
00:35:33,477 --> 00:35:35,911
But you did.

475
00:35:35,979 --> 00:35:38,614
And there's nothing you can do
to change that.

476
00:35:38,682 --> 00:35:42,853
Only thing you can change is
your future.

477
00:35:42,920 --> 00:35:44,621
Right?

478
00:35:46,591 --> 00:35:48,893
No? You're probably scared.

479
00:35:48,961 --> 00:35:51,062
You probably feel

480
00:35:51,129 --> 00:35:54,198
- like you're all alone.
- I'm not alone.

481
00:35:54,266 --> 00:35:57,703
That's right.
You're not alone. Nothing has

482
00:35:57,771 --> 00:36:00,806
happened in our relationship that
you and I can't...

483
00:36:11,346 --> 00:36:13,547
I was looking forward to that.

484
00:36:13,614 --> 00:36:16,517
I saved you the trouble.

485
00:37:02,304 --> 00:37:03,905
Ah!

486
00:37:11,816 --> 00:37:13,884
Ah!

487
00:37:40,282 --> 00:37:42,216
Ahhh!

488
00:39:00,674 --> 00:39:05,012
I was worried you were dead.

489
00:39:08,449 --> 00:39:10,084
Tobias Budge

490
00:39:10,151 --> 00:39:13,855
killed two
Baltimore police officers,

491
00:39:13,923 --> 00:39:15,891
nearly killed
an FBI special agent,

492
00:39:15,958 --> 00:39:19,061
and after all of that,
his first stop

493
00:39:19,129 --> 00:39:21,330
is here, at your office.

494
00:39:21,398 --> 00:39:24,601
He came to kill my patient.

495
00:39:24,668 --> 00:39:29,106
Your patient. Is that
who Budge was serenading?

496
00:39:29,173 --> 00:39:32,075
I don't know.

497
00:39:32,143 --> 00:39:34,512
Franklyn knew more

498
00:39:34,579 --> 00:39:37,181
than he was telling me.
He told Mr. Budge

499
00:39:37,249 --> 00:39:39,351
that he didn't have
to kill anymore.

500
00:39:42,188 --> 00:39:45,090
And then he broke Franklyn's
neck, and then he attacked me.

501
00:39:45,158 --> 00:39:47,260
You killed him?

502
00:39:49,230 --> 00:39:50,663
Yeah.

503
00:39:50,731 --> 00:39:53,834
Could Franklyn have been
involved

504
00:39:53,902 --> 00:39:56,704
in whatever Budge was doing?

505
00:39:56,772 --> 00:40:01,209
I thought this was a simple
matter of poor choice in friends.

506
00:40:01,277 --> 00:40:03,645
This doesn't feel simple to me.

507
00:40:16,127 --> 00:40:17,928
I feel like I've...

508
00:40:17,996 --> 00:40:20,198
dragged you into my world.

509
00:40:20,266 --> 00:40:22,000
I got here on my own.

510
00:40:22,068 --> 00:40:25,938
But I appreciate the company.

511
00:40:37,485 --> 00:40:40,021
I'm going to start
seeing patients again.

512
00:40:42,858 --> 00:40:48,197
It's strange, thinking about
going back to daily practice.

513
00:40:48,264 --> 00:40:51,266
Well, it's good
you stepped away.

514
00:40:51,334 --> 00:40:54,170
Even if it was
only for a few days.

515
00:40:54,238 --> 00:40:57,875
Patients will sit
where Franklyn died.

516
00:40:59,844 --> 00:41:03,314
I will sit where I almost died,
and I will offer therapy.

